Package: detect
Type: Package
Title: Analyzing Data with Detection Error Based on Single Visit
Version: 1.1-0
Date: 2011-08-08
Author: Peter Solymos, Monica Moreno, Subhash R Lele
Maintainer: Peter Solymos <solymos@ualberta.ca>
Depends: R (>= 1.7.0)
Suggests: dclone, pbapply
Description: The package implements zero inflated Binomial model
  for single visit site occupancy and Binomial-ZIP mixture model 
  for single visit count data when the probability of detection
  is less than one. Provides hands-on formula interface with inferences
  based on numerical optimization and data cloning.
  Development was funded by the Alberta Biodiversity Monitoring Institute.
License: GPL-2
URL: http://dcr.r-forge.r-project.org/, http://www.abmi.ca/
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: true
